An excellent app that turns your Android device into a hand bearing compass. I was about to spend $50 to buy one for my boat. . . .  This app on my Droid 3 is accurate to within a couple of degrees, tested against landmarks near me. Very impressive.  For users who think it's way off, or who feel that north moved, etc. -- try calibrating your phone's compass. Use "Settings" > "Initialize sensors," then do the calibration move: Rotate your phone twice slowly around all 3 of its axes. Makes a big difference in accuracy. You may need to do this every time you open the app -- but it can be done in about 15 seconds and is worth the trouble. Do it away from all cars, metal, iron-bearing rocks, etc.  I also find that I get a different bearing depending on whether the camera mode is on or off (probably some small current going to the camera effects the magnetic reading) -- so you have to decide on one or the other, and initialize the sensors for that state. I love camera-on! Very cool app.
